{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"comely-craven-apatosaur","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Problem\nThe `rebar-brainstorm` skill (examples/agent-skills/rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md) tells the\nauthor to run the plan-review gate on *each* ticket immediately after creating them, before\nany dependency links exist and regardless of blocked state. This contradicts the actual gate\nbehavior documented in AGENTS.md / docs/plan-review-gate.md: `rebar review-plan` fast-fails\nwith no LLM (unsigned INDETERMINATE, exit 2) on a ticket that is not yet claimable — one still\n`open` but blocked by an unclosed dependency — and reviews are dependency-scoped so they must\nrun in dependency order (prerequisites/children before dependents), never in parallel.\n\n## Approach\nRewrite the \"Before recording tickets, read the project's plan-review gate\" section of\nrebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md so that, after creating tickets, the author FIRST establishes the\ndependency graph between children (link via blocks/depends_on), then runs plan-review ONLY on\nunblocked tickets (identified by `rebar ready`), in dependency order, reviewing later tickets\nas their dependencies close and they become unblocked. Rationale: authoring to the real gate\nprotocol avoids a guaranteed no-LLM fast-fail and matches AGENTS.md's dependency-order review\nrule; it is far cheaper than discovering the exit-2 at review time.\n\nAlso assess rebar-implement/SKILL.md: it is an executor of an already-decomposed epic and\nalready claims/reviews only the unblocked, dependency-ordered set via `rebar ready`/\n`next-batch`, treating the dependency graph as a precondition — so it needs no change. This\nassessment is part of the ticket's scope (documented outcome: no edit).\n\n## Acceptance criteria (in-session, verifiable)\n1. rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md's plan-review section states plan-review is run only on unblocked\n   tickets, after the child dependency graph (blocks/depends_on links) is established, in\n   dependency order — verifiable by reading the edited section.\n2. The section references the no-LLM fast-fail on still-blocked tickets and `rebar ready` for\n   identifying the unblocked set.\n3. rebar-implement/SKILL.md is left unchanged, with the assessment rationale recorded on this\n   ticket as a comment.\n4. Change lands on main through Gerrit (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1).","id":"4819-5f75-d931-4b44","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"rebar-brainstorm: run plan-review only on unblocked tickets after dependency graph is established"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784868946932795001,"uuid":"d27d2ed4-7e2a-4985-a5af-8941d1121e50"}